<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-970-578  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 970 578.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Software Engineering  Nov 1989 v15 n11p1333(14).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mapping the interface description language type model into C.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shannon, Karen; Snodgrass, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Interface Description Language (IDL) describes thecharacteristics of data structures passed among a group ofcooperating processes and supports such abstract data types assets and sequences for any type, including all necessary datadeclarations and data manipulation routines.andP;  Mapping the IDLstructure specifications into data structure declarations of the Cprogramming language is examined.andP;  The mapping should support thefull IDL language, should cause violations of the IDL type modelto cause violations of the C type model (and vice versa), shouldnot make great resource demands on the C compiler, should beruntime efficient in both space and time, and should present agood user interface to the programmer.andP;  The mapping needed to meetall five criteria is proposed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Program Development TechniquesNew TechniqueTechnologyC Programming LanguageInterfaceData StructuresCompilersProgram Translators.andO;Feature:   illustrationprogramchart.andO;Caption:   Process and class type declarations. (program)Use of the IDL translator. (chart)Use of the new preprocessor. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>